laboratory_examinations.findings: Dysplastic bone demonstrated the typical histopathologic appearance of fibrous dysplasia.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: After autoclaving, significant deformation of dysplastic cells without destruction of the noncellular frame was observed. Histopathologic examination of a piece of the previously placed autoclaved dysplastic bone graft three years after indicated fibrovascular connective tissue with viable osteocytes; no signs of recurrence.
